# Plan: Replace string-template path building with path.join over segments

## Context

`src/config/agents.ts` stores agent paths as hand-authored strings with hard-coded OS separators (e.g. `"{home}\\.claude\\skills\\{name}"` for Windows). `src/core/resolve.ts:105` then assembles final paths via `.replace()` on those strings. This is fragile: a new agent entry with a wrong separator character would silently produce a broken path on Windows only, with no type-system or runtime guard.

The fix: replace path strings with **arrays of segments** and join them via `path.join()`, which always uses the correct OS separator automatically.

## Changes

### 1. `src/types.ts` — `AgentPaths` type
```ts
// Before
export interface AgentPaths {
  posix: string;
  windows: string;
}

// After
export interface AgentPaths {
  posix: string[];
  windows: string[];
}
```

### 2. `src/config/agents.ts` — convert all path strings to segment arrays

Each path becomes an array of path components. Placeholders (`{home}`, `{name}`, `{appdata}`) stay but live in individual segments — no separator characters in any string.

Example (Claude Code):
```ts
skills: {
  posix: ["{home}", ".claude", "skills", "{name}"],
  windows: ["{home}", ".claude", "skills", "{name}"],
},
detectPaths: {
  posix: ["{home}", ".claude"],
  windows: ["{home}", ".claude"],
},
```

